[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Width-to-height aspect ratio of the viewport.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Number of bits per color component of the output device, or zero if the device isn't color.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Approximate range of colors that are supported by the user agent and output device.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Number of entries in the output device's color lookup table, or zero if the device does not use such a table.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Width-to-height aspect ratio of the output device.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Height of the rendering surface of the output device.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Detects the device's current posture, that is, whether the viewport is in a flat or folded state.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Width of the rendering surface of the output device.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] The mode in which an application is being displayed: for example, fullscreen or picture-in-picture mode.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Combination of brightness, contrast ratio, and color depth that are supported by the user agent and the output device.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Detect whether user agent restricts color palette.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Does the device use a grid or bitmap screen?
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Detects whether the device has a specified number of viewport segments laid out horizontally.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Does the primary input mechanism allow the user to hover over elements?
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Is the user agent or underlying OS inverting colors?
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Bits per pixel in the output device's monochrome frame buffer, or zero if the device isn't monochrome.
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] How does the output device handle content that overflows the viewport along the block axis?
[src:viewport-responsive/css-media] Can content that overflows the viewport along the inline axis be scrolled?
